  <Markdown id="intro">
## Hidden Block

**Advanced / System-Level Block**

Hidden includes children in the content tree without displaying them. Content is accessible programmatically (e.g., by LLMs scanning the page) but invisible to users.
  </Markdown>

  <Markdown id="example_intro">
### Example: Hidden Context for AI

Below, an LLM could access the hidden rubric when analyzing the response, but students only see the question and input:
  </Markdown>

  <Vertical id="essay_example">
    <Markdown id="question">Explain the water cycle.</Markdown>
    <Hidden>
      <Markdown id="rubric">
**Rubric (hidden from students):**
- Mentions evaporation, condensation, precipitation
- Describes cyclical nature
- Uses appropriate terminology
      </Markdown>
    </Hidden>
    <TextArea id="response" placeholder="Write your explanation..." rows="4" />
  </Vertical>

</Vertical>
